definitions.definition: Tending to resist something or someone; resistant .
examples: He had a stubborn, resistive nature.

definitions.definition: Acting as a resistor ; resisting the passage of electrical current .
Of an electronic circuit : consisting only of resistors and power sources ; having no inductance and capacitance .

main_definition: ( rare ) Tending to resist something or someone; resistant .
